19/03/2006
UZICE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Four children from the western Serbian town of Bajina Basta are in hospital with bird flu-like symptoms in Uzice, authorities said in a statement Friday (17 March). 
Earlier this month, the presence of the deadly H5N1 virus strain was detected in a dead swan and a rooster in the Bajna Basta area. 
According to the statement, the children had been in contact with infected poultry. 
In addition, 24 other people from the same region are under observation. 
(Danas, Tanjug, B92 - 18/03/06)
